            They play a vital role in supporting overall wellness by contributing to improved immunity, 
            healthy aging, enhanced vitality, and general body nourishment. Numerous studies have shown 
            that individuals who include adequate amounts of fresh vegetables in their daily meals tend 
            to enjoy better long-term health and improved resistance to common ailments.
            Farmgate Nigeria is proud to pioneer a fully integrated digital marketplace that connects 
            vegetable farmers directly with consumers, retailers, wholesalers, and event planners across 
            the country. Our platform is the first of its kind in Nigeria—designed specifically to empower
         vegetable growers and provide buyers with easy, unrestricted access to fresh, locally grown 
         produce.
        </p>
        <h3 class="aboutHead">For Vegetable Farmers</h3>
        <p>
        This is a call to all vegetable farmers nationwide: Farmgate Nigeria offers you a ready-made 
        online marketplace where you can showcase your produce to thousands of buyers who are actively 
        searching for fresh leafy and fruity vegetables. Whether you grow in small, medium, or large 
        quantities, our platform ensures your products reach the right customers at the right time.
      </p>
        <h3 class="aboutHead">For Buyers & Event Planners</h3>
        <p>

        
        Planning a large event or stocking up for commercial food preparation? Farmgate Nigeria gives you 
        direct access to trusted vegetable sellers and farmers in every region of Nigeria. You can 
        conveniently order bulk quantities of leafy vegetables such as:<br>
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Jute mallow (Ewedu)</li>
          <li>Spinach</li>
          <li>Celosia</li>
          <li>Amaranthus</li>
          <li>Waterleaf</li>
          <li>Fluted pumpkin (Ugu)
        </ul>
        Perfect for preparing soups like Ewedu, Efo-Riro, and other traditional delicacies.
        We also offer seamless access to bulk orders of fruity vegetables including:<br>
        <ul>
          <li>Tomatoes</li>
          <li>Peppers</li>
          <li>Cucumbers</li>
          <li>Garden eggs</li>
          <li>Eggplants</li>
          <li>Onions</li>
        </ul>
        Ideal for salads, stews, sauces, catering services, and party menus.
        <h3 class="aboutHead">Our Commitment</h3>
        At Farmgate Nigeria, our priority is to ensure that consumers enjoy fresh, unadulterated farm 
        produce sourced directly from farmers—without preservatives, middlemen, or foreign additives. 
        We aim to make high-quality vegetables affordable and accessible to households, restaurants, 
        markets, and event planners across the country, all at true farm-gate prices.
        Farmgate Nigeria is your trusted link to reliable vegetable farmers and quality produce—fresh 
        from the farm to your doorstep.
        </div>

            <div class="add-new">
                <button><a href="/vegetables/addnew">Add to vegetables</a></button>
                <p>List of the available agrocommodities for sales</p>
            </div>
            <div class="general-content">
              <%if(veggies.length === 0){%>
            <div class="no-products">
                <p>No product at the moment, please check back later</p>
            </div>
        <%}else{%>
            <%veggies.forEach(function(veg){%>
                <div class="content">
                    <a href="/vegetables/<%=veg._id%>">
                        <img height="auto" width="100%" src="<%= veg.image[0].url%>" alt="a batch of farm fresh <%=veg.name%> for sell"/>
                        <div class="content-desc">
                            <h3><%=veg.name%></h3>
                            <p><%=veg.description%></p>
                            <p>currency: Naira</p>
                          <p>price: =N=<%=veg.price%></p>
                        </div>
                        <button class="frontBtn">See more</button>
                    </a>
                    
                </div>
            <%})%>
            <%}%>
        </div>
        
                <div class="pagination">
                  <% if (currentPage > 1) { %>
                      <a href="/vegetables?page=<%= currentPage - 1 %>" class="page-btn">Previous</a>
                  <% } %>

                  <% for (let i = 1; i <= totalPages; i++) { %>
                      <a href="/vegetables?page=<%= i %>" 
                        class="page-number <%= i === currentPage ? 'active' : '' %>">
                          <%= i %>
                      </a>
                  <% } %>

                  <% if (currentPage < totalPages) { %>
                      <a href="/vegetables?page=<%= currentPage + 1 %>" class="page-btn">Next</a>
                  <% } %>
              </div>
</div>
<%- include("../partials/footer")%>
    
